<p>Rebecca Murphey is a senior software engineer at Bazaarvoice and a frequent speaker on the topics of code organization and best practices at conferences around the world. She’s also the creator of the TXJS conference, the author of the learning site jQuery Fundamentals, a contributor to the jQuery Cookbook from O’Reilly Media, and a technical reviewer for Effective JavaScript by Dave Herman. She blogs at <a href="http://lanyrd.com/2012/full-frontal/sztqh/">rmurphey.com</a>, tweets as <a href="https://twitter.com/rmurphey">@rmurphey</a>, and lives in Durham, NC, with her partner.</p>
